# AI-Powered Demand Forecasting & Smart Operations Center

## Description

AI-Powered Demand Forecasting & Smart Operations Center is an intelligent analytics platform designed to help businesses optimize inventory management, demand planning, and operational decision-making.

Built with Python and Streamlit, the application enables users to upload Excel datasets and generate actionable insights through predictive analytics, inventory evaluation, financial impact assessments, and AI-assisted procurement recommendations.

The platform combines statistical forecasting techniques with operational performance metrics to support data-driven business decisions.

## Technologies

The project is built using the following technologies:

* Python
* Streamlit
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Scikit-learn
* Plotly
* OpenPyXL

## Features

### Demand Forecasting

* AI-assisted demand prediction
* Future sales estimation
* Trend-based forecasting models
* Linear Regression analysis

### Inventory Management

* Inventory level monitoring
* Critical stock identification
* Reorder planning support
* Inventory optimization insights

### EOQ (Economic Order Quantity)

* Automated EOQ calculations
* Order cost optimization
* Inventory holding cost analysis

### Financial Impact Analysis

* Revenue projections
* Inventory cost estimation
* Business performance evaluation
* Profitability insights

### Operational Health Score

* Operational risk assessment
* Inventory efficiency evaluation
* Product performance analysis
* Overall operational scoring system

### Smart Procurement Recommendations

* AI-generated purchasing suggestions
* Procurement scheduling support
* Inventory replenishment recommendations

### Interactive Data Visualization

* Dynamic charts and dashboards
* Plotly-powered visual analytics
* Real-time KPI monitoring

## Installation

### Prerequisites

Before running the application, ensure you have:

* Python 3.10 or later
* Required Python libraries installed

### Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/ai-demand-forecasting-center.git

cd ai-demand-forecasting-center
```

### Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install streamlit pandas numpy scikit-learn plotly openpyxl
```

### Run the Application

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

## Usage

### Step 1: Launch the Application

Start the Streamlit server and open the provided local URL in your browser.

### Step 2: Upload an Excel File

Upload an Excel file containing inventory and product information.

### Step 3: Analyze Data

The system automatically processes the uploaded dataset and generates:

* Demand forecasts
* Inventory evaluations
* EOQ calculations
* Financial impact reports
* Operational health scores

### Step 4: Review Insights

Use the interactive dashboard to explore forecasts, recommendations, and operational metrics.

## Supported Excel Format

The uploaded Excel file should contain at least the following columns:

### Required Fields

```text
Product Name
Stock Quantity
```

### Optional Fields

```text
Sales Price
```

Additional fields can be included to enrich forecasting and analysis capabilities.

## System Modules

### Demand Forecasting Module

Uses Linear Regression techniques to estimate future demand and sales trends based on available data.

### EOQ Calculation Module

Determines the optimal order quantity to minimize inventory and procurement costs.

### Operational Health Assessment

Analyzes inventory risks and operational efficiency to generate an overall health score.

### Financial Impact Analysis

Calculates projected revenue, inventory value, and potential business impact.

### Scenario Simulation Engine

Supports demand simulations based on various external factors, including:

* Currency exchange fluctuations
* Weather conditions
* Seasonal effects
* Housing market trends

These simulations help organizations evaluate potential future scenarios and prepare strategic responses.

